text: Bridget Layburn (born 27 June 2001) is a New Zealand water polo player. She competed for the New Zealand women's national water polo team in the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. She was educated at Westlake Girls High School. She played for the University of Hawaii's women's water polo team. == References == == Other websites == * bridget-layburn swimswam * hawaii-water- polo-rainbow-wahine Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand water polo players
